description:
mrigger added on 2020-02-28 14:49:21:
Consider the following test case:
CREATE VIRTUAL TABLE rt0 USING rtree(c0, c1, c2);
INSERT INTO rt0(c0) VALUES (0);
CREATE VIEW v0(c0) AS SELECT DISTINCT rt0.c1 FROM rt0;
SELECT v0.c0 FROM v0, rt0 WHERE v0.c0 = rt0.c1; -- expected: 0.0, actual: 0
Unexpectedly, the value of v0.c0 is 0, rather than 0.0. When removing the WHERE clause the correct value is fetched:
SELECT v0.c0 FROM v0, rt0; -- 0.0
